CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper April 22, 1961, pg. 10, reads: "Librarian Assists - Miss Marjorie T. Franklin helps an avid reader, Charles Henry, find a book suitable to his tastes, at the Carnegie Library in Pittsburgh, where she is employed. She holds the title of senior librarian, though she began 10 years ago as a clerical assistant."
TitMainTitle: Senior librarian Marjorie T. Franklin pulling book off shelf for Charles Henry in Carnegie Library of Pittsburgh
